Former president Jacob Zuma’s son, Duduzane, has confirmed arranging a meeting between Former Deputy Finance Minister Mcebisi Jonas and the Gupta family. Duduzane Zuma has taken the stand at the Commission of Inquiry into State Capture, In Parktown, Johannesburg. Jonas has previously testified that Duduzane introduced him to the controversial family at their Saxonworld home in 2015. He says one of the Gupta brothers offered him the position of finance minister for R600 million. Evidence leader, Advocate Phillip Mokoena  is leading Zuma’s evidence.  Watch Duduzane on the stand: 